OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A British national living in the UK has
OL,6, been accused by police in Hong Kong of 
OL,7, jeopardising China's national security 
OL,8, and told he faces three years in jail. 
OL,10,FBenedict Rogers runs Hong Kong Watch, a
OL,11,Fcharity which campaigns for human      
OL,12,Frights in the former British colony.   
OL,14,FBut he has been informed that he faces 
OL,15,Fcharges of "collusion with foreign     
OL,16,Fforces" if he ever returns there.      
OL,18,FForeign Secretary Liz Truss said the   
OL,19,Fthreat was "unjustifiable". Mr Rogers  
OL,20,Fsaid his group would not be silenced.  
